org.openflow.protocol

Class OFMatch20

  • java.lang.Object
    • org.openflow.protocol.OFMatch20
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    java.lang.Cloneable

    public class OFMatch20
extends java.lang.Object
implements java.lang.Cloneable
    Represents an ofp_match_msg.

    Using OFMatch20 instead of OFMatch in POF. OFMatch20 describes a field of a protocol or a field of a packet. Different with OFMatch message which contains certain protocol information such as mac/ip/port, OFMatch20 just uses fieldId, offset and length to present a field. So users could use several OFMatch20 to create a total new protocol or packet type.

    Author:
    Song Jian (jack.songjian@huawei.com), Huawei Technologies Co., Ltd.
